        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:53PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Akron to near North
Manchester to near La Fontaine. Movement was northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntington, Warsaw, Wabash, North Manchester, Winona Lake, South
Whitley, Akron, Andrews, Pierceton, Silver Lake, Roann, Claypool,
Lagro, Larwill, Burket, Sidney, Big Barbee Lake, Ridinger Lake,
Collamer, and Liberty Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for central, north
central and northeastern Indiana.</instruction>
